1. PURPOSE OF THIS LICENSE

This software is provided for personal, private, local execution only.

Commercial usage, public hosting, redistribution, or resale is not permitted without written approval and a commercial license.

2. FREE USAGE CONDITIONS

You may use the software free of charge only if ALL below are true:

- It runs locally on a personal device
- It is accessed only by you (single user)
- It does NOT run on a public domain or external network
- You are not charging money for its usage
- You are not providing workflows to business clients
- It is not deployed inside a business or institutional infrastructure
- It is not used to automate tasks for others

Examples allowed:

- http://localhost:3000
- http://127.0.0.1:PORT
- Private device usage

Examples NOT allowed without paid license:

- domain.com
- dev.company.local
- Internal company server
- Shared VPS
- Shared office installation

3. HOSTED OR PUBLIC DEPLOYMENT REQUIREMENTS

If deployed outside localhost:

A clear attribution MUST appear visibly:

Built using FlowMason — https://github.com/chavanashutosh/flowmason

This attribution must be:

- readable
- included in UI footer or about page
- not hidden or minimized

Additionally:

- branding and original name cannot be removed or replaced
- "FlowMason" must remain visible

4. COMMERCIAL RESTRICTIONS

Without a commercial license you may NOT:

- sell access to FlowMason
- run it as SaaS for customers
- include it inside paid systems
- charge clients for workflows executed using FlowMason
- deploy in corporate environments
- deliver automation services that rely on it
- monetize integrations developed inside FlowMason

Commercial use requires direct agreement with the licensor.

5. MODIFICATIONS AND CONTRIBUTIONS

This project is open to contributors. Contributions are welcome through Pull Requests to the original repository at https://github.com/chavanashutosh/flowmason.

You may modify the software under these conditions:

- modifications remain private
- you must submit them as Pull Requests to the original repository when requested
- you must contribute improvements upstream
- you must not publish modified versions as independent repositories

You may NOT:

- fork the repository publicly
- publish derivative repo
- send modified version to others

Any derivative work must remain under this same license.

6. NO FORKS, MIRRORS OR DISTRIBUTION

The following actions are expressly prohibited:

- public forks
- reposting source code or binaries
- distributing copies privately or publicly
- sublicensing to others
- repackaging under a different name

The original repository remains the only valid source distribution.

7. TELEMETRY & IDENTIFICATION

If telemetry is later included, you consent to:

- anonymized usage tracking
